# REST API Conventions

## URLs & versioning

- Prefix public APIs with `/api/v1/`.
- Use plural nouns: `/api/v1/items`, not `/api/v1/item`.
- Use path variables for resource IDs; query params for filters/pagination.

## HTTP semantics

| Action | Method | Status |
|--------|--------|--------|
| Create | POST | 201 Created + `Location` header |
| Read | GET | 200 OK |
| Update | PUT/PATCH | 200 OK |
| Delete | DELETE | 204 No Content |
| Not found | — | 404 via `ResourceNotFoundException` |
| Validation error | — | 400 via `@Valid` + `@ControllerAdvice` |

## Request validation

- Annotate request bodies with `@Valid`.
- Use Jakarta Bean Validation on DTOs (`@NotBlank`, `@NotNull`, `@Size`, `@Email`).

```java
// BAD — no validation, returns entity
@PostMapping
public Item create(@RequestBody Item item) { ... }

// GOOD
@PostMapping
public ResponseEntity<ItemResponse> create(@Valid @RequestBody ItemRequest request) {
  var created = itemService.create(request);
  return ResponseEntity.created(URI.create("/api/v1/items/" + created.id())).body(created);
}
```

## Error responses

- Use a consistent error body (e.g. `ApiError` record) from `@RestControllerAdvice`.
- Do not leak internal exception messages or stack traces to clients.
